reviewText: These are two of my very favorite movies.  They arrived in perfect condition.  I am going to enjoy them for a long time to come.
Title: Guarding Tess/It Could Happen To You

reviewText: Both movies are fun Cage movies where he plays the long suffering "Mr Nice Guy" who has his ups and downs as he pokes along with his job (secret service protector to ex-Presidents' widow in "Guarding Tess" and beat cop in "It Could Happen to You").  OK for the whole family, though there is some violence in "Guarding Tess" that could disturb youngsters.
summary: Sweet movies to spend time with; nothing really challenging, but fun
Title: Guarding Tess/It Could Happen To You

reviewText: We ave been slowly upgrading our videos to DVDs and we were happy to find this set, taking care of two movies at once.  We love the humor and emotion in GUarding Tess and It Could Happen to You is just a delightful true story where the good guy wins.
Title: Guarding Tess/It Could Happen To You

reviewText: both are Nickolas Cage Movies that are not Marine Hero type...both are testing the resolve with compassion.  They are a lesson in integrity and gaining and losing.  It is like a lot of my movies; one that shows a person learning there is more than meets the eye.  All the characters experience something they had not expected in values.
Title: Guarding Tess/It Could Happen To You

reviewText: I love this movie and decided to buy it on DVD as my VHS player no longer works.  It is a great movie and more of a dream for most of us but we can dream, can't we!
